tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: Most parameters are within normal limits. Notable findings include mild leukopenia, elevated hemoglobin and MCHC, and low urine specific gravity. These may suggest mild dehydration or hemoconcentration. No evidence of renal dysfunction, diabetes, or urinary tract infection. Clinical correlation and follow-up are recommended, especially regarding the cause of leukopenia and elevated hemoglobin.
